<h2 id="en-appendix-editorial-note">Appendix: Editorial Note</h2>
<p>The textual basis of the ATP quotations is an OCR digitisation of the Massumi edition (University of Minnesota Press 1987). All page numbers were verified against the running heads of the digitisation; quotations crossing a page break are marked with double references (e.g. ATP 12–13). Individual pages missing or truncated in the digitisation (pp. 309, 350, 423, 473, 500) were checked by the project lead directly against the PDF print master; the passages quoted from them count as verified. Obvious OCR artefacts were corrected tacitly (e.g. "black hoes" for "black holes", "deterritorializaton" for "deterritorialization"). Before any print publication, all quotations are to be collated against the printed edition; this applies in particular to passages that sit at a page break in the digitisation. Quotations from the secondary literature follow the sources documented in the reading notes; for Mersch 2015 the reservation on the typescript status noted above applies. The revision of the state of research (ch. 3) rests on a two-stage search: in a first step, around eighty titles from the author's collection were surveyed; in a second, the canonical texts carrying the argument were studied in depth — partly in full text, partly verified only bibliographically; in the bibliography, titles that could not be consulted in full text are given without page references and flagged with a note of uncertainty.</p>
<p>Revision note v3 (July 2026). Compared with version v2, the following were added on the basis of a critical full review: a failure criterion for the transposition (ch. 2); the placement of Schön, Barrett/Bolt and Smith/Dean within the methodology debate (ch. 3.1); the clarification of the model's status as a process grammar, together with a problem-finding section (ch. 5); the instrument economy, per-instrument failure criteria, a constructed negative example (T6) and the trial protocol (ch. 6); the reflexive turn of the quality criteria (ch. 7); and two additional objections — the discursivisation problem and the economy objection — with the renumbering of the problem zones (ch. 8). The six postulates and the eight instruments themselves are unchanged in substance. Open tasks before any submission: Manning/Massumi 2014, Cotter 2019 and Schwab 2013 are to be worked through in full text (so far accessed via reviews or verified only bibliographically); Schön 1983 and Smith/Dean 2009 are cited without page references and are to be verified against the editions before print; the dating and pagination questions flagged in the bibliography remain open.</p>`
